main event: A witness in Davenport, Iowa reported seeing an unidentified flying object on May 11, 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10 minutes.
The observer has a significantly high reliability rating based on previous analysis of their observations.
The object's motion is described as 'On Level' and 'Yes (returned)'.
The report indicates there was no physical evidence collected.
The conclusion of the report is that the object was 'UNIDENTIFIED'.
